AIM:
To design and implement a Login System using HTML, JavaScript, PHP, and MySQL.The system validates user input on the client-side and checks login credentials from a MySQL database.

PROCEDURE:
Create database logindb in MySQL Workbench.
Create table users and insert sample login credentials.
Design login page using HTML and CSS.
Add JavaScript validation for user inputs.
Write backend PHP script (login.php) to check credentials with database.
Run the project using XAMPP/WAMP.
Test login with valid and invalid data.

code:
1)Database:
CREATE DATABASE logindb;

USE logindb;

CREATE TABLE users (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(100),
    password VARCHAR(100)   -- store plain for demo; use hashing in real apps
);

2)login.html

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Login System</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: Arial; background: #f0f0f0; }
        .box {
            width: 300px; margin: 50px auto; padding: 20px;
            background: #fff; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 0 10px #ccc;
        }
        input {
            width: 100%; padding: 10px; margin: 8px 0;
            border-radius: 5px; border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }
        button {
            width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: #007bff;
            color: white; border: none; border-radius: 5px;
        }
        #error { color: red; margin-top: 10px; }
    </style>

    <script>
        function validateForm() {
            let user = document.getElementById("username").value;
            let pass = document.getElementById("password").value;
            let error = document.getElementById("error");

            if (user === "" || pass === "") {
                error.innerHTML = "All fields are required!";
                return false;
            }

            if (pass.length < 5) {
                error.innerHTML = "Password must be at least 5 characters!";
                return false;
            }

            return true;
        }
    </script>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="box">
        <h2>Login</h2>

        <form action="login.php" method="post" onsubmit="return validateForm();">
            <input type="text" id="username" name="username" placeholder="Enter Username">

            <input type="password" id="password" name="password" placeholder="Enter Password">

            <button type="submit">Login</button>

            <p id="error"></p>
        </form>
    </div>
</body>
</html>

3)login.php

<?php
$conn = mysqli_connect("localhost", "root", "Jeevaakash123@", "logindb");

if (!$conn) {
    die("Connection Failed: " . mysqli_connect_error());
}

$user = $_POST['username'];
$pass = $_POST['password'];

$sql = "SELECT * FROM users WHERE username='$user' AND password='$pass'";
$result = mysqli_query($conn, $sql);

if (mysqli_num_rows($result) > 0) {
    echo "<h2>Login Successful! Welcome, $user</h2>";
} else {
    echo "<h2>Invalid Username or Password!</h2>";
    echo "<a href='login.html'>Try Again</a>";
}

mysqli_close($conn);
?>

